<p>This DroboApp deploys <?php echo $appname; ?> on your Drobo.</p>
<p>Network File System (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_File_System" target="_new"><?php echo $appname; ?></a>) is a distributed file system protocol, allowing a user on a client computer to access files over a local network much like local storage is accessed.</p>
<p><?php echo $appname; ?> is an alternative to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Server_Message_Block" target="_new">SMB</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Filing_Protocol" target="_new">AFP</a>, which are both supported natively on the Drobo.</p>
<p><?php echo $appname; ?> is usually deployed in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix" target="_new">Unix</a> environments, such as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux" target="_new">Linux</a> machines.</p>